<p>Run command on multiple files at once</p>

<p>For example: all files in a directory:</p>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>for FILE in $(ls *); do command $FILE; done
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Warning: this assumes there are no spaces in the lines in your file. If they do # contain spaces, you need to add proper escaping using quotes.</p>

<p><strong>Describe Better</strong></p>

